What a nuts, busy weekend, but so good. MagicCon, Indiana Dunes National Park, exploring Chicago with Griffin Museum, Willis Tower, Shedd Aquarium, and The Bean! Ben and his brothers got to do their first trip together, ever, and it made me so happy to see them all hang and just be brothers, no other roles attached to them. And in the most me fashion, I escaped the city for a day to spend time in nature with people I love. Oh‚Ä¶ also.. OTTERS?!!! ü¶¶ Meeting them was a lifelong goal of mine and I don‚Äôt think it‚Äôs possible to be more obsessed with them. The Lupos conquered Chicago!

Iron Lung is officially showing in theaters today! It has been awesome sharing the music with you this week and I will be sharing more as I create some "How it was made" shorts for here. Thank you so much for the support and I hope you enjoy the film!

Artwork by: @deadlymelodic 
Render by: @lixiantv

"PTSD" was really just inspired by Marks performance. He portrays the "5 stages of grief" REALLY well but I personally identified with the specific scene this music was made for. He nails it and I wanted to do my best to make sure he had something to match it behind him.

Artwork by @deadlymelodic 
Render by @lixiantv 

Ironlung.com to find a theater near you!

"The Shakes" was written on set on my laptop about 50 ft away from Mark while he was performing the last shots of the film. After we listened back to it we both agreed that it would be the motif of the film. It uses a large piece of sheet metal being oscillated with a theragun as the lead instrument.

Artwork: @deadlymelodic 
Render: @lixiantv 

The film comes out Jan 30th!
Check ironlung.com for a theater near you!

I tried a new idea for the Iron Lung soundtrack. I took a bunch of samples of pieces of old iron/metal ect. being bent/twisted/vibrated and pitched them around in @presonus Studio One and put them in a granular synthesizer. They became the "strings" section for the soundtrack :-)

Hello! 

Hope all is well. 

I wanted to share some thoughts about the past, the present and the future. 

The topics of this post will be Los Ratones 2025, Twitch + YouTube, LEC 2026 Versus and Worlds co-streaming. 

The past: 

For those who remember, when I made the choice to participate in Los Ratones and discontinue my journey in Korea I was looking for a mix between playing and taking a break as I felt quite troubled after the 2021 - 2023 seasons. 2024 was an incredible year for me with T1, but I was looking for an opportunity to be closer to home. That part worked out as planned in 2025, I feel like I am in a really good place mentally now and ready for whatever is to come. No more baggage from the past weighing me down. When it comes to League of Legends I would say this season also lived up to expectations, we won almost all we could win whilst still enjoying the process for the majority of the year at the same time. I think towards the end some of the more positive spirit started to disappear, and this is something we need to discuss as a group how to make it better moving forward. The positivity from many of you was a big help, and I really appreciated the support and encouragement towards myself, the other players and coaches. Thank you to everyone that cheered for us and I hope that you can keep cheering for us in 2026 as we compete in LEC Versus.

The present: 

With EMEA finished there is Worlds co-streaming and the Red Bull event left before we enter the 2026 preparation period. I will be covering the remaining games of Worlds (friendly reminder Quarterfinals start tomorrow), then taking 2 weeks vacation in Patagonia to rest and recover before departing to Munich. Once that is done I will take a break from Twitch + YouTube as I want to fully focus on what I can do to make our coming months a success and as much as I have enjoyed streaming and posting videos it does not make sense for me to do everything simultaneously due to my autism diagnosis.

To be continued in comments!

It is with great pleasure I announce I will be co-streaming Worlds 2025.

I did something similar 3 years ago for Worlds 2022 and really enjoyed watching that together with all of you, so I‚Äôm extremely happy to be doing it once again.

Friendly reminder that some of the games are scheduled to overlap with EMEA Masters so I will most likely not be able to cover everything, but promise to do my best to be there as much as possible.

Thanks so much to Riot for entrusting me with this opportunity. Make sure to follow my Twitch to catch all the action live, and I‚Äôll also be uploading all the games I cover on my YouTube for anyone who missed out.
